vifm (an ncurses-based file manager with Vim-like everything)

Vifm is a file manager with curses interface, which provides Vim-like
environment for managing objects within file systems, extended with
some useful ideas from mutt.  If you use vi, Vifm gives you complete
keyboard control over your files without having to learn a new set of
commands.

Vim users: A vifm.vim plugin is included in /usr/share/vifm/vim/.
Read /usr/doc/vifm-$VERSION/README_vim.txt for usage information.
